[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
#Kai
But here's a thing, An.[p]
Human is a strange creature. Three days ago i turned off the survival machine on a 60 years old woman.[p]
For the last 5 years we've been trying to tell her family there's no hope for her to wake up anymore.[p]
But they kept trying and trying until they couldn't afford the bill no more. Just because they couldn't bare to kill her.[p]
And yet when i talked to her as a Death's Messenger, she said the last 5 years was the most painful thing she's ever been through, it was hell itself.[p]
I told her about her family and she was thankful for how much they loved her. But her last wish was for none of them to suffer the same pain that she did.[p]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
#Kai
Just this morning, we had a case of a husband and wife burned for gas explosion. We couldn't save the husband.[p]
I appeared in front of him as a Death's Messenger and told him this is his final judgement day. [p]
He either has the chance to go to the next life or exchange his soul for a wish. If he takes the offer with me, i can change reality itself for him.[p]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
#Kai
And yet all he asked for was to tell his wife to dig up a box he burried under their oak tree backyard.[p]
We managed to save the wife but couldn't save the baby inside her. After telling her what happened, we had to spend the next two hours trying to stop her from committing suicide.[p]
She said the gas explosion was her fault. She killed her husband and their baby.[p]
She burned down the house with everything they owned and now her appearance was also ruined, she couldn't look at herslef anymore. [p]
She couldn't find a reason to continue living. That was when i told the wife that her husband asked her to dig up the box under the oak tree.[p]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
The tree was burned down just like the rest of the house but the box was still there.[p]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
Inside it were letters, pictures, little wooden gifts he made, memories and "i love you" notes for his wife.[p]
The husband planned to give it to her in their next anniversary. The wife bursted out crying and said she could live to the next 100 years just with this.[p]

[_tb_end_text]

